From: OpenAI Codex <codex@openai.com>
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: freescale: dpaa: add flowtable offload support

Add DPAA flowtable offload support with these pieces:

- bind to the stock `TC_SETUP_FT` flowtable hook
- compile supported flowtable rules into driver-owned records
- validate matches and actions up front and reject unsupported shapes
  with per-reason counters
- index installed flows by exact ingress tuple for runtime lookup
- execute precompiled Ethernet rewrite, TTL or hop-limit decrement, and
  exact IPv4 NAT when present in the compiled rule
- forward matched packets through a fresh skb path
- expose delayed install, hit, fallback, and reject visibility in sysfs
- add compile-time guards for reject and fallback name tables

This patch adds the install-time data model and the initial packet
execution path for compiled flowtable entries.

